## Package Manager

Always use **pnpm**. Never npm or yarn.

```bash
pnpm dev              # Start backend + frontend in parallel
pnpm build            # Build all packages
pnpm typecheck        # Type-check all (tsc --noEmit)
pnpm test             # Run all tests
pnpm lint             # ESLint + Stylelint
pnpm format           # Prettier

# Per-package
pnpm -F @xomda/node dev      # Backend only (port 3000)
pnpm -F @xomda/client dev    # Frontend only (port 5173)
pnpm -F @xomda/diagram dev   # Storybook (port 6006)
```

## Monorepo Structure

```
@xomda/core       → Zod schemas, types, constants (source of truth)
@xomda/util       → Runtime utilities
@xomda/template   → Handlebars engine + template storage
@xomda/model      → tRPC router, business logic, CRUD
@xomda/node       → Node.js HTTP server
@xomda/client     → Vue 3 SPA (Vuetify 4, Pinia, Vue Router)
@xomda/diagram    → Vue 3 diagram components (Storybook)
@xomda/icons      → Material Symbols icons
@xomda/ui         → Generic UI components (DynamicForm, TitleBar, etc.)
@xomda/codeeditor → Monaco Editor for template editing
@xomda/analysis-core → Project analysis framework
@xomda/plugin-analysis-* → Technology detectors
```

**Dependency graph** (no cycles allowed):
```
client → model → template → core
client → diagram → icons
client → codeeditor
node   → model
```

Use `workspace:*` in `package.json` to reference local packages.

## TypeScript

- **Strict mode** — no `any`, use `unknown` + narrowing or generics
- **Import type syntax** — separate type imports from values
- **Explicit return types** — all public functions must declare return types

## Vue Components

- **Use `.tsx` files** — no `.vue` SFC files
- **Named exports only** — no default exports
- **Use `defineComponent`** for proper type inference
- **SCSS modules** for component styles (`*.module.scss`)

## Formatting & Quality

```bash
pnpm format           # Prettier (2-space, no semicolons, single quotes, 100 char width)
pnpm lint             # ESLint (TypeScript rules + import sorting)
```

## Testing

Always add tests when adding functionality:
- **Vitest** for unit tests
- **Storybook** for component documentation
- **Cypress** for E2E tests

For more details, see the linked knowledge base files above.
- **`import type`** for type-only imports (ESLint rule enforces this)
- **No SFC files** — all Vue components are `.tsx`
- **`moduleResolution: "bundler"`** for browser packages; `"NodeNext"` for server packages

## Vue Component Style

No `.vue` SFCs. All components use `defineComponent` with TSX:

```typescript
import { defineComponent, ref } from 'vue'
import styles from './MyComponent.module.scss'

export const MyComponent = defineComponent({
  name: 'MyComponent',
  props: {
    title: { type: String, required: true },
  },
  setup(props) {
    const count = ref(0)
    return () => (
      <div class={styles.root}>
        <h2>{props.title}</h2>
        <button onClick={() => count.value++}>{count.value}</button>
      </div>
    )
  },
})
```

**Named exports only** — no `export default` for components.

## File & Folder Organisation

- **One component per file** — never define multiple components in a single `.tsx` file
- **Folder per composite component** — when a component uses extracted sub-components, move all into a folder with an `index.ts`:
  ```
  components/
    CellEditor/
      index.ts           ← exports only the public API (e.g. CellEditor)
      CellEditor.tsx     ← main component
      OutputCellForm.tsx ← internal sub-component (not re-exported)
  ```
- **`index.ts` for every folder** — export only what is public; never `export *` everything
- **Prefer index imports** — `import { X } from './X'` not `import { X } from './X/X'`
- **No file extensions** — never use `.ts` or `.tsx` in import paths

## Styling

- **SCSS modules** (`*.module.scss`) for all component styles
- Import: `import styles from './Component.module.scss'`
- No global CSS except Vuetify 4 theme overrides

## tRPC

**Router (backend)**:
```typescript
import { z } from 'zod'
import { publicProcedure, router } from './trpc'

export const myRouter = router({
  list: publicProcedure.query(() => readItems()),
  create: publicProcedure.input(ItemSchema).mutation(({ input }) => createItem(input)),
})
```

**Client**:
```typescript
import { trpc } from '../trpc'
const items = await trpc.model.listEntities.query()
await trpc.model.addEntity.mutate({ entity, packageId })
```

Router namespaces: `model.*`, `template.*`, `file.*`

## Zod Schemas

All schemas live in **`@xomda/core`** — never define shared schemas in `@xomda/model` or other consumer packages.

